(632, NULL, NULL, 27, 13, 'This is my day, a banal day.\nI get up, take my breakfast looking at my tweet-list, today Trump insults Kim Jong-un with Twitter! How can a President speak this way?\nAfter one little moment to imagine Trump and Kim Jong-un around a part of Civilization V.\nI learn the discovery of a flaw in the Minix operating system hidden in the Intel CPU, I read next \"An Open Letter to Intel\" by Andrew S. Tanenbaum for Mr. Krzanich . Power makes crazy, for what purpose put a backdoor and for who ?\nToday, the neutrality of the web is a utopian idea and computer equipment is pierced from all sides ... It\'s disgusting and revolting at the same time !\nFortunately, that some people are fighting against the Big Brothers of our time.\nThis little bitter finding to close my breakfast, I take my PC to check the tracking of my Banggood package, still in Roissy.\nI start Visual Studio is starting my new project, a cryptonote miner. Why?\nFor the challenge and out of curiosity, the low-level optimization part, the network and mathematical protocol is fascinating.\nTo avoid reinventing the wheel, I will start from an existing project.\nIn all sincerity I do not know what to say about my day.\nSo I\'ll tell you some fun facts about computer virus protection.\nI experiment a little antivirus, detection means, virtualization systems, only for education of course.\nI have long sought to make an executable file (FUD) indectectable. (only for education once again !)\nOnly we are not more in the 90s, changing the digital signature of a file is not enough.\nThe scans are now static and dynamic.\nSo I tested, when an antivirus scans a file, it has two rather important constraints, time of execution and resources use.\nMany security companies respect the saying \"Time is money\".\nI think the numbers of words is good.'),
