(4757, NULL, NULL, 201, 13, 'What did I do today? Let see...I woke up shocked to see the trees across my window bending under the strong wind that was blowing outside, ate breakfast, got dressed, and started to learn how to code php using the codecademy learning website. I had a hard time finding a php course because it is not display with the regular learning skills options. I had to research the web for it but eventually I was lucky and got directed to a php course on codecademy written in french! The strange part is that I got php badges in my profil account for the php tutorials I took but the fact that I\'m taking a php course is not showing on the completed skills area. Really weird!\n After that I decided to check the inscription for SIMPLON Web developer training and discovered that I needed to learn php on a different website that codecademy which was not written in the e-mail I received from \"pôle emploi\". So now, I guess I have to check this new learning website and start to earn php badges over again. \nAfter training my mind, I decided to train my body as well and drove to the gym where I took a crossfit class first to work hard my muscles, followed by a yoga class to work on my flexibility and my zen attitude. I\'m the type of person who cannot go through a week without doing any sport. It is my therapy I guess. I would say it\'s much better and healthier that taking alcohol or valium to relax. After that, I drove to the convenient store and bought some fruits to make myself a smoothie. Did you notice how health concerned people tend to become after doing sport? For me, it\'s like I\'m turning a switch inside my mind which reorganized my thoughts to follow a healthy path. So, as soon as I reached home, I made myself a healthy greenish snack. \nThis summarize part of my day which is, by the way, not over yet.\n'),
(4758, NULL, NULL, 201, 14, 'Intégrer la formation développeur.se Web serait un vrai plus dans mon CV. En effet, il y a une forte demande pour des développeurs.ses front-end en général mais particulièrement dans les métiers liés au design web et à l\'ergonomie web. On m\'a souvent demandé lors d\'interviews si je savais intégrer mon travail et je pense ne pas avoir était retenue de nombreuses fois à cause de mon incapacité à coder. Pourquoi engager 2 personnes pour faire un travail alors que l\'on peut en engager qu\'une. C\'est une réponse qu\'il m\'a été donné lors d\'un entretien d\'embauche lorsque j\'ai pointé le fait qu\'un.e  UX designer n\'était pas un développeur.se web.'),
